Mapping.ExpertSettingsSg:
# Mask static secrets (passwords and alike) in WAF logs and policy learning data ParameterMasking.Enable "TRUE" ParameterMasking.Name.Pattern "^#json#(?:.*)?(?:password|password|oldPassword|newPassword|answer|otp|firstOtp|secondOtp|challengeResponse)$" ParameterMasking.Name.IgnoreCase "FALSE" ParameterMasking.Name.InvertPattern "FALSE"
# Change default content type from application/x-www-form-urlencoded to application/json, such that # bodiless POST requests to the REST API are allowed. DefaultPostRequestContentType "application/json"
Mapping.ExpertSettingsApache: # Ensure that a CSRF-Block is redirected to a URL that returns 403 to be intercepted by IAM Loginapp UI RewriteEngine On RewriteRule "invalid/csrf-token" "-" [F]

The security level Standard further prevents injection of SQL sub queries and SQL expressions in single quote context (e.g. ' or 1=1--). The security level Strict further prevents SQLi in unquoted context (e.g. 1 or 1).

SoftLink.Description: All headers not explicitly contained in the whitelist of well-known headers are removed.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10000]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Request header whitelist

SoftLink.Description: Some headers known to be problematic are removed.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10002]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Request header blacklist

SoftLink.Description: The value in the incoming host header is replaced by the back-end host. Rewriting the host header may be necessary if the application server needs the back-end host name in the header instead of the external name (e.g. for name based virtual hosts in the back-end).
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10003]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Translate Host header

SoftLink.Description: The incoming referer header is rewritten to match the back-end protocol/host/URL. Rewriting the referer may be necessary if the application interprets the referer field but is not reverse-proxy compatible.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10004]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Translate Referer header

SoftLink.Description: The incoming origin header is rewritten to match the back-end protocol/host/URL. Rewriting the origin may be necessary if the application interprets the origin field but is not reverse-proxy compatible.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10007]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Translate Origin header

SoftLink.Description: Adds an X-Forwarded-For header to preserve the original client IP for back-ends.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10005]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add X-Forwarded-For header

SoftLink.Description: Adds an X-Forwarded-Proto header to preserve the original protocol for back-ends.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalRequestHeaderAction[ID=-10006]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add X-Forwarded-Proto header

SoftLink.Description: All headers not explicitly contained in the whitelist of well-known headers are removed.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20000]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Response header whitelist

SoftLink.Description: Removes some unused headers.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20002]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Response header blacklist

SoftLink.Description: Some headers leak information about back-end servers and deployed software. By removing these headers, such information is hidden from potential attackers.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20003]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Response header blacklist (information leakage)

SoftLink.Description: Back-ends can advise clients to authenticate using NTLM. By default, these headers are removed, because NTLM passthrough is not supported. When using front-side NTLM in combination with an authentication service, this action must be disabled.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20004]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Remove NTLM header

SoftLink.Description: Back-end can advise clients to authenticate using a specific method. By default, these headers are removed. This action must be disabled when using front-side Kerberos in combination with an authentication service.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20005]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Remove Negotiate header

SoftLink.Description: CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a method for enabling cross-origin requests in browsers. If misconfigured, CORS reduces client-side security. This action removes CORS headers that have no restrictions.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20006]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Remove permissive CORS header

SoftLink.Description: If no X-Frame-Options are specified by the back-end, this action advises browser to display a page only in a frame with the same origin as the page itself. This prevents clickjacking attacks.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20007]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add X-Frame-Options header

SoftLink.Description: HSTS headers advise browsers to use solely secure HTTPS connections towards the back-end. If no HSTS header is specified by the back-end, this actions adds a default HSTS header, requiring HTTPS for all requests.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20009]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS) header

SoftLink.Description: Content Security Policy (CSP) is a technique for preventing Cross-Site-Scripting and similar attacks by restricting the origin of included resources in a website. Defining fine-grained policies requires good knowledge of the application. If no CSP headers are specified by the back-end, this action adds a base protection, allowing inclusion of Javascript and image resources only from the back-end itself.
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20010]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add Content-Security-Policy (CSP) header

SoftLink.Description: See action "(default) Add Content Security Policy (CSP) header" (variant with an "X-" prefix).
SoftLink.Link: GlobalResponseHeaderAction[ID=-20011]
SoftLink.DisplayName: (default) Add Content-Security-Policy (CSP) header (with prefix "X-")

SoftLink.Description: If no corresponding header is present, this actions enables the XSS protection feature of IE 8 browsers (and newer).
